cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG

The paper discusses an environment for automated reasoning on the basis of first-order logic, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of Prolog and the focus on formulas suggest that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) are the most likely sub-categories. The use of macros and LaTeX-formatted natural language text suggests cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) as possible sub-categories. Finally, the discussion of features and limitations suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
